{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"33272ccd-8ca0-4581-b5d7-f11e0ff60ef3","content":"Here are the MSBuild evaluation performance issues in this project:\n\n---\n\n### 1. Recursive wildcard glob (`**\\*.*`) — **High impact**\n```xml\n<AdditionalFiles Include=\"**\\*.*\" Exclude=\"**\\bin\\**;**\\obj\\**\" />\n```\nThe `**\\*.*` glob forces MSBuild to walk the **entire directory tree** during evaluation. This is one of the most expensive evaluation-time operations, and it scales with the number of files on disk (including `node_modules`, artifacts, etc.). Prefer explicit paths or narrower globs (e.g., `docs\\*.md`).\n\n---\n\n### 2. File I/O via property function — **Medium-high impact**\n```xml\n<BuildNotes>$([System.IO.File]::ReadAllText('build-notes.txt'))</BuildNotes>\n```\n`ReadAllText` executes **during evaluation**, not during build. Property functions that perform file I/O block the evaluator and bypass MSBuild's caching. This should be moved to a target (using `ReadLinesFromFile` task) that runs at build time, or removed entirely.\n\n---\n\n### 3. Deep import chain — **Medium impact**\n```\nEvalHeavy.csproj → level1.props → level2.props → level3.props\n```\nThree levels of chained imports. Each import adds an XML parse + evaluation pass. While three levels is moderate, this pattern tends to grow over time and compounds with the SDK's own imports. Flatten where possible.\n\n---\n\n### Summary (priority order)\n\n| Issue | Pattern | Fix |\n|---|---|---|\n| Recursive glob | `**\\*.*` | Narrow the glob or list files explicitly |\n| Property-function I/O | `File::ReadAllText` | Move to a build-time target |\n| Chained imports | 3 levels deep | Flatten into fewer files |\n\nThe recursive glob is by far the biggest offender — in a repo with thousands of files it can add seconds to every evaluation (IDE load, `dotnet build`, etc.).","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"fff877d4-52d0-4472-b3da-a22e6818fd00","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"Now I have a clear picture of the project. Let me analyze the MSBuild evaluation performance issues.","outputTokens":519},"id":"5026650d-329d-4d4c-a07e-3e581bcae449","timestamp":"2026-04-08T01:09:45.849Z","parentId":"88ac2398-e9d6-47c5-9dbe-af1a43ef2a5b"}
